- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses solving problems on structures of bounded treewidth, which is a common concept in data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper discusses tree automata and their construction. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses an implementation of the proposed approach. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses a novel approach to solving problems that could have applications in AI.
